'''Cleopatra''' (in [[Ancient Greek|Greek]] ''Κλεοπάτρα'') means ''glory of her father''. It derives from ''Κλέος'' (=''glory'') and ''Πατρός'', genitive case of ''Πατήρ'' (=''father''). Its masculine form is ''Κλεόπατρος'' &amp;ndash; ''Cleopatros''

''Cleopatra'' may refer to:

== Historic ==
* [[Cleopatra Vibe of Eleanor]]
* [[Cleopatra I Syra]]
* [[Cleopatra II of Egypt]]
* [[Cleopatra III of Egypt]]
* [[Cleopatra IV of Egypt]]
* [[Cleopatra V of Egypt]]
* [[Cleopatra VI of Egypt]]
* [[Cleopatra VII|Cleopatra VII of Egypt]], famed lover of [[Mark Antony]]
** has been the subject of many [[cultural depictions of Cleopatra VII|cultural depictions]]
* [[Cleopatra Eurydice of Macedon]], wife of [[Philip II of Macedon]]
* [[Cleopatra of Jerusalem]], wife of [[Herod the Great]]
* [[Cleopatra of Macedon]], daughter of Cleopatra Eurydice and Philip II
* [[Cleopatra of Pontus]], wife of [[Tigranes the Great]]
* [[Cleopatra Selene I]], daughter of Cleopatra III and [[Ptolemy VIII Physcon]]
* [[Cleopatra Selene II]], daughter of Cleopatra VII and [[Mark Antony]]
* [[Cleopatra Thea]], daughter of Cleopatra II and [[Ptolemy VI Philometor]]
* [[Saint Cleopatra]]

== Mythology ==
