===Air quality===
According to [http://scorecard.org Scorecard.org], Merrimack County ranked in 2002 among the top 10% dirtiest in terms of air pollution, with a total release of {{convert|2830473|lb}} of toxins, compared to {{convert|543|lb}} in neighboring [[Belknap County, New Hampshire|Belknap County]]. The top chemical pollutant release was [[hydrochloric acid]] at {{convert|2300000|lb}}, followed by [[sulfuric acid]] with {{convert|340000|lb}} released.  The majority of toxins, {{convert|2746211|lb}}, were released in the neighboring town of [[Bow, New Hampshire|Bow]] at the Merrimack Station power plant.

The [http://des.nh.gov/ New Hampshire Department of Environmental Services] has put an air quality forecast page on their website. In comparing scorecard.org and the [http://www2.des.state.nh.us/airdata/air_quality_forecast.asp NHDES pollutant forecast], there has been an improvement in air quality from 2002 to 2011.

==Demographics==
