===Mayor===
In May 2009, [[John Gormley]], the [[Minister for the Environment, Heritage and Local Government]], announced plans to have a directly-elected &quot;Mayor of Dublin&quot; from 2010, whose powers would be similar to those of the [[Mayor of London]], and whose authority would extend to all four local authority areas within the historic county of Dublin.&lt;ref&gt;
{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/dublin-to-get-first-directly-elected-mayor-by-next-year-1736938.html |title=Dublin to get first directly elected mayor by next year |last=Molony |first=Senan |date=13 May 2009 |work=[[Irish Independent]] |accessdate=2009-05-13}}&lt;/ref&gt; The Mayor would chair the [[Dublin Transport Authority]].&lt;ref&gt;
{{cite news |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2009/0512/breaking75.htm |title=Dublin to elect mayor next year |last=Edwards |first=Elaine |date=12 May 2009 |work=[[The Irish Times]] |accessdate=2009-05-13}}
&lt;/ref&gt; The existing [[Lord Mayor of Dublin]] is the chair of the City Council, a position which is elected annually.

==Media==
* The local radio stations include [[98FM (Ireland)|98FM]], [[FM104]], [[Dublin City FM|103.2 Dublin City FM]], [[Dublin's Q102]], [[Spin 1038]], [[Dublin's Country Mix 106.8]], [[Phantom FM|Phantom 105.2]] and [[Radio Nova 100FM (Ireland)|Radio Nova]].

* The local newspapers include ''[[Dublin Penny Journal]]'', ''[[The Echo (Irish newspaper)|The Echo]]'', ''[[Northside People|The Northside People]]'', ''[[Southside People|The Southside People]]'', ''[[Liffey Champion]]'' and ''[[Metro (Associated Metro Limited)|Metro]]''.

Most of the area can receive the five main UK television channels on analogue television as well as the main Irish channels, along with Sky TV and UPC cable television. 

==Transport==
*'''Road:''' The major roads are the  [[N2 road (Ireland)|N2]], [[N3 road (Ireland)|N3]], [[N4 road (Ireland)|N4]] and [[N7 road (Ireland)|N7]] national primary roads, and the [[M1 motorway (Republic of Ireland)|M1]], [[N11 road (Ireland)|M11]] and [[M50 motorway (Ireland)|M50]] motorways.

*'''Heavy rail:''' The [[InterCity (Iarnród Éireann)|InterCity]] and [[Commuter (Iarnród Éireann)|Commuter]] rail services ([[Iarnród Éireann]]).

*'''Light rail:''' The [[Luas]] tram system serving [[Dublin|Dublin City]] and its suburbs.

*'''Rapid transit:''' The [[Dublin Area Rapid Transit|DART]] and the proposed [[Dublin Metro]] line.

*'''Port:''' [[Dublin Port]] and [[Dún Laoghaire| Dún Laoghaire Harbour]].

*'''Air:''' [[Dublin Airport|Dublin International Airport]].

